properties.abstract: A circular route starting in Delémont that rapidly leads up to the hills north of town. Spectacular vantage points with views of the valley, such as Côte-à-Bépierre, line the path. The descent after the Col des Rangiers takes you through pastures, forests and hamlets typical of the Jura landscape.
properties.description:
The route starts from Delémont railway station and heads northwards through the city, past the beautiful old town with its colourful houses. Shortly afterwards, you reach Le Bambois. From here, the path runs across fields and sparse forests to the Côte-à-Bépierre vantage point, where the sweeping views over the valley are well worth a look.

The route continues to climb to La Haute-Borne, an ideal resting place with beautiful views over the verdant Jura hills. After that, the terrain is more or less flat until the Col des Rangiers. From there, you begin to descend, passing through the village of Montavon with its old farms to the hamlet of Les Lavoirs.

There is one last steep climb to negotiate before you reach Haut du Bois and continue leisurely on a path along the forest edge. On the final stretch, you pass the Château de Domont. The small castle is now a restaurant with a sunny terrace where you can rest and refuel with your feet in the grass. Passing through the town's western neighbourhoods, you reach Delémont railway station.
